1. bis triceni. From the number invited and the style of the dinner, we may conclude that it was one of those quasi- official dinners given by great mento their cliente, an occasional invitation to which was part of the payment for the services rendered. Such a dinner is described in the fifth satire of Juvenal. Generally in these cases the triclinium of the host which he occupied with a few friends of his own degree, was served quite differently from the other triclinia where the clients were.
